Both outputs are now written and validated:

- **`transcript.json`** — 10 iterations conforming to `transcript_schema.json` (validated). Each iteration contains self-contained hypotheses naming specific columns and signed directions, plus analyses with `hypothesis_ids`, `effect_estimate`, `p_value`, and `significant` fields.
- **`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative synthesis covering the strongest individual predictors, the central treatment-by-biomarker pattern (feature_038 confers +2.74 mo PFS benefit only when feature_013, feature_043, and feature_109 are all negative — the canonical predictive-biomarker signature), the prognostic features (feature_078, 051, 057, 092, 099, 009, 006), and the comprehensive null findings on demographic disparities (race and insurance).

The final 12-term OLS model achieves R² = 0.91, with the treatment-by-biomarker interaction term contributing +2.74 months and the resistance markers having no main effect (they exist only as effect modifiers).
